OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1780481194
OL,3,CHealth Secretary: I would no longer
OL,4,Csay trans women are women
OL,6,FHe said he had thought "in quite some
OL,7,Fdetail" about use of language, when it
OL,8,Fwas put to him that he had in the past
OL,9,Fstated that "trans women are women".
OL,11,FAsked if he had changed his mind, he
OL,12,Ftold BBC Radio 4's Today programme:
OL,13,F"Yeah, I have changed what I would
OL,14,Fsay. I wouldn't say that phrase any
OL,15,Fmore.
OL,17,F"And I think that, you know, over the
OL,18,Flast few years, I think a lot of us,
OL,19,Fmyself included, have thought about
OL,20,Fthis question in quite some detail.
OL,26,@nD@XOUoD@GO]qD@MOUqD@cO]uD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1780481194
OL,3,CHealth Secretary: I would no longer
OL,4,Csay trans women are women
OL,6,F"The Supreme Court has obviously ruled
OL,7,Fvery clearly that biological sex is
OL,8,Fwhat matters when it comes to the
OL,9,FEquality Act, and determining the
OL,10,Fimportance of single-sex spaces."
OL,12,FHe stressed that he also believes in
OL,13,F"dignity for trans people".
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@aO]uD@AOUuD@ZO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1780481194
OL,3,CHealth Secretary: I would no longer
OL,4,Csay trans women are women
OL,6,FHe added: "I believe that single-sex
OL,7,Fspaces should be protected on the
OL,8,Fbasis of sex, on the basis of
OL,9,Fbiological sex, whilst at the same
OL,10,Ftime believing in dignity for trans
OL,11,Fpeople, recognising that sex and
OL,12,Fgender are different things, but being
OL,13,Fabsolutely clear that single-sex
OL,14,Fspaces within the NHS, for instance,
OL,15,Fneed to be protected on the basis of
OL,16,Fsex."
OL,26,@nD@KOUxD@EO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/9
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
